058/**
059 *  The default implementation for
060 *  {@link MapStream MapStream}.
061 *
062 *  @param  <K> The type of the map keys.
063 *  @param  <V> The type of the map values.
064 *
065 *  @author Alexis Cartier (alexcrt)
066 *  @modified Thomas Thrien - thomas.thrien@tquadrat.org
067 *  @version $Id: DefaultMapStream.java 995 2022-01-23 01:09:35Z tquadrat $
068 *  @since 0.0.7
069 *
070 *  @UMLGraph.link
071 */
072@ClassVersion( sourceVersion = "$Id: DefaultMapStream.java 995 2022-01-23 01:09:35Z tquadrat $" )
073@API( status = INTERNAL, since = "0.0.7" )
074public final class DefaultMapStream<K,V> implements MapStream<K,V>
075{
076        /*------------*\
077    ====** Attributes **=======================================================
078        \*------------*/
079    /**
080     *  The wrapped stream.
081     */
082    private final Stream<Entry<K,V>> m_Delegate;
083
084        /*--------------*\
085    ====** Constructors **=====================================================
086        \*--------------*/
087    /**
088     *  Creates a new {@code DefaultMapStream} instance from the provided
089     *  stream.
090     *
091     *  @param  stream  The stream to wrap.
092     */
093    public DefaultMapStream( final Stream<Entry<K,V>> stream ) { m_Delegate = requireNonNullArgument( stream, "stream" ); }
094
095        /*---------*\
096    ====** Methods **==========================================================
097        \*---------*/
098    /**
099     *  {@inheritDoc}
100     */
101    @Override
102    public final boolean allMatch( final Predicate<? super Entry<K,V>> predicate ) { return m_Delegate.allMatch( predicate ); }
103
104    /**
105     *  {@inheritDoc}
106     */
107    @Override
108    public final boolean anyMatch( final Predicate<? super Entry<K,V>> predicate ) { return m_Delegate.anyMatch( predicate ); }
109
110    /**
111     *  {@inheritDoc}
112     */
113    @Override
114    public final void close() { m_Delegate.close(); }
115
116    /**
117     *  {@inheritDoc}
118     */
119    @Override
120    public final <R,A> R collect( final Collector<? super Entry<K,V>,A,R> collector ) { return m_Delegate.collect( collector ); }
121
122    /**
123     *  {@inheritDoc}
124     */
125    @Override
126    public final <R> R collect( final Supplier<R> supplier, final BiConsumer<R,? super Entry<K,V>> accumulator, final BiConsumer<R,R> combiner )
127    {
128        return m_Delegate.collect( supplier, accumulator, combiner );
129    }   //  collect()
130
131    /**
132     *  {@inheritDoc}
133     */
134    @Override
135    public final long count() { return m_Delegate.count(); }
136
137    /**
138     *  {@inheritDoc}
139     */
140    @Override
141    public final MapStream<K,V> distinct() { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.distinct() ); }
142
143    /**
144     *  {@inheritDoc}
145     */
146    @Override
147    public final MapStream<K,V> filter( final Predicate<? super Entry<K,V>> predicate )
148    {
149        return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.filter( predicate ) );
150    }   //  filter()
151
152    /**
153     *  {@inheritDoc}
154     */
155    @Override
156    public final Optional<Entry<K,V>> findAny() { return m_Delegate.findAny(); }
157
158    /**
159     *  {@inheritDoc}
160     */
161    @Override
162    public final Optional<Entry<K,V>> findFirst() { return m_Delegate.findFirst(); }
163
164    /**
165     *  {@inheritDoc}
166     */
167    @Override
168    public final <R> Stream<R> flatMap( final Function<? super Entry<K,V>,? extends Stream<? extends R>> mapper )
169    {
170        return m_Delegate.flatMap( mapper );
171    }   //  flatMap()
172
173    /**
174     *  {@inheritDoc}
175     */
176    @Override
177    public final DoubleStream flatMapToDouble( final Function<? super Entry<K,V>,? extends DoubleStream> mapper )
178    {
179        return m_Delegate.flatMapToDouble( mapper );
180    }   //  flatMapToDouble()
181
182    /**
183     *  {@inheritDoc}
184     */
185    @Override
186    public final IntStream flatMapToInt( final Function<? super Entry<K,V>,? extends IntStream> mapper )
187    {
188        return m_Delegate.flatMapToInt( mapper );
189    }   //  flatMapToInt()
190
191    /**
192     *  {@inheritDoc}
193     */
194    @Override
195    public final LongStream flatMapToLong( final Function<? super Entry<K,V>,? extends LongStream> mapper )
196    {
197        return m_Delegate.flatMapToLong( mapper );
198    }   //  flatMapToLong()
199
200    /**
201     *  {@inheritDoc}
202     */
203    @Override
204    public final void forEach( final Consumer<? super Entry<K,V>> action ) { m_Delegate.forEach( action ); }
205
206    /**
207     *  {@inheritDoc}
208     */
209    @Override
210    public final void forEachOrdered( final Consumer<? super Entry<K,V>> action ) { m_Delegate.forEachOrdered( action ); }
211
212    /**
213     *  {@inheritDoc}
214     */
215    @Override
216    public final boolean isParallel() { return m_Delegate.isParallel(); }
217
218    /**
219     *  {@inheritDoc}
220     */
221    @Override
222    public final Iterator<Entry<K,V>> iterator() { return m_Delegate.iterator(); }
223
224    /**
225     *  {@inheritDoc}
226     */
227    @Override
228    public final MapStream<K,V> limit( final long maxSize ) { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.limit( maxSize ) ); }
229
230    /**
231     *  {@inheritDoc}
232     */
233    @Override
234    public final <R> Stream<R> map( final Function<? super Entry<K,V>,? extends R> mapper ) { return m_Delegate.map( mapper ); }
235
236    /**
237     *  {@inheritDoc}
238     */
239    @Override
240    public final DoubleStream mapToDouble( final ToDoubleFunction<? super Entry<K,V>> mapper ) { return m_Delegate.mapToDouble( mapper ); }
241
242    /**
243     *  {@inheritDoc}
244     */
245    @Override
246    public final IntStream mapToInt( final ToIntFunction<? super Entry<K,V>> mapper ) { return m_Delegate.mapToInt( mapper ); }
247
248    /**
249     *  {@inheritDoc}
250     */
251    @Override
252    public final LongStream mapToLong( final ToLongFunction<? super Entry<K,V>> mapper ) { return m_Delegate.mapToLong( mapper ); }
253
254    /**
255     *  {@inheritDoc}
256     */
257    @Override
258    public final Optional<Entry<K,V>> max( final Comparator<? super Entry<K,V>> comparator ) { return m_Delegate.max( comparator ); }
259
260    /**
261     *  {@inheritDoc}
262     */
263    @Override
264    public final Optional<Entry<K,V>> min( final Comparator<? super Entry<K,V>> comparator ) { return m_Delegate.min( comparator ); }
265
266    /**
267     *  {@inheritDoc}
268     */
269    @Override
270    public final boolean noneMatch( final Predicate<? super Entry<K,V>> predicate ) { return m_Delegate.noneMatch( predicate ); }
271
272    /**
273     *  {@inheritDoc}
274     */
275    @Override
276    public final MapStream<K,V> onClose( final Runnable closeHandler ) { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.onClose( closeHandler ) ); }
277
278    /**
279     *  {@inheritDoc}
280     */
281    @Override
282    public final MapStream<K,V> parallel() { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.parallel() ); }
283
284    /**
285     *  {@inheritDoc}
286     */
287    @Override
288    public final MapStream<K,V> peek( final Consumer<? super Entry<K,V>> action ) { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.peek( action ) ); }
289
290    /**
291     *  {@inheritDoc}
292     */
293    @Override
294    public final Optional<Entry<K,V>> reduce( final BinaryOperator<Entry<K,V>> accumulator ) { return m_Delegate.reduce( accumulator ); }
295
296    /**
297     *  {@inheritDoc}
298     */
299    @Override
300    public final Entry<K,V> reduce( final Entry<K,V> identity, final BinaryOperator<Entry<K,V>> accumulator )
301    {
302        return m_Delegate.reduce( identity, accumulator );
303    }   //  reduce()
304
305    /**
306     *  {@inheritDoc}
307     */
308    @Override
309    public final <U> U reduce( final U identity, final BiFunction<U,? super Entry<K,V>,U> accumulator, final BinaryOperator<U> combiner )
310    {
311        return m_Delegate.reduce( identity, accumulator, combiner );
312    }   //  reduce()
313
314    /**
315     *  {@inheritDoc}
316     */
317    @Override
318    public final MapStream<K,V> sequential() { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.sequential() ); }
319
320    /**
321     *  {@inheritDoc}
322     */
323    @Override
324    public final MapStream<K,V> skip( final long n ) { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.skip( n ) ); }
325
326    /**
327     *  {@inheritDoc}
328     */
329    @Override
330    public final MapStream<K,V> sorted() { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.sorted() ); }
331
332    /**
333     *  {@inheritDoc}
334     */
335    @Override
336    public final MapStream<K,V> sorted( final Comparator<? super Entry<K,V>> comparator ) { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.sorted( comparator ) ); }
337
338    /**
339     *  {@inheritDoc}
340     *  @see java.util.stream.BaseStream#spliterator()
341     */
342    @Override
343    public final Spliterator<Entry<K,V>> spliterator() { return m_Delegate.spliterator(); }
344
345    /**
346     *  {@inheritDoc}
347     */
348    @Override
349    public final Object [] toArray() { return m_Delegate.toArray(); }
350
351    /**
352     *  {@inheritDoc}
353     */
354    @SuppressWarnings( "SuspiciousToArrayCall" )
355    @Override
356    public final <A> A [] toArray( final IntFunction<A []> generator ) { return m_Delegate.toArray( generator ); }
357
358    /**
359     *  {@inheritDoc}
360     */
361    @Override
362    public final MapStream<K,V> unordered() { return new DefaultMapStream<>( m_Delegate.unordered() ); }
363}
